1
00:00:01,666 --> 00:00:03,333
[♪]

2
00:01:11,733 --> 00:01:13,666
Whoa, I'm stuffed.

3
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,566
That was delicious, Mom.

4
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,200
Glad you
liked it, dear.

5
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:18,433
Now, if you
ask your father,

6
00:01:18,466 --> 00:01:19,800
maybe he'll help you
with your homework.

7
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:22,200
I'd rather
hear a story.

8
00:01:22,233 --> 00:01:24,166
Father,
tell me more

9
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,600
about the legend
of the Blue Knight.

10
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:28,400
FATHER:
Homework first,
stories later.

11
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:30,533
Hmm... Oh.

12
00:01:30,566 --> 00:01:32,600
Try this, Emily.

13
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:35,333
If you calculate pi
to the billionth digit,

14
00:01:35,366 --> 00:01:37,600
you can construct
a five-dimensional algorithm.

15
00:01:37,633 --> 00:01:40,033
Whoa! Five dimensions!

16
00:01:40,066 --> 00:01:41,066
Next
I'll show you

17
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,500
how to do
six dimensions.

18
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:45,266
All right!

19
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:46,366
O'SHAY:
As you can see,

20
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,633
their feelings
are virtually identical

21
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:49,466
to human emotions.

22
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,733
WOMAN:
That's the beauty
of these prototypes.

23
00:01:51,766 --> 00:01:53,300
By monitoring
their systems,

24
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:54,566
we learn what life
will be like

25
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,033
for humans in space,

26
00:01:56,066 --> 00:01:57,066
physically and emotionally.

27
00:01:57,100 --> 00:02:00,066
Someday we'll send real families
to live in space,

28
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,366
in colonies
like this.

29
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,533
These robot families
are helping to pave the way.

30
00:02:03,566 --> 00:02:06,266
WOMAN:
But when we give them
human emotions,

31
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:07,633
don't you think
we have a responsibility

32
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:09,266
for what happens to them?

33
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:10,733
MAN:
Now, don't get
carried away.

34
00:02:10,766 --> 00:02:13,166
These robots don't really
care about each other.

35
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,500
It's just a simulation.

36
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:16,466
After all, they
are only machines.

37
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,066
Arrgh! Arrgh!

38
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:19,566
What is going on?

39
00:02:26,566 --> 00:02:27,733
Space raiders!

40
00:02:27,766 --> 00:02:29,033
MAN:
Oh, great.

41
00:02:29,066 --> 00:02:31,366
This will ruin
my experiment!

42
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,200
Forget
your experiment!

43
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:35,433
Those robots
are in serious danger.

44
00:02:35,466 --> 00:02:39,200
O'SHAY [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Astro, come in!</i>
<i>Astro, do you read me?</i>

45
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:42,066
I copy you, doctor.
What's up?

46
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,200
O'SHAY:
<i>Space raiders</i>
<i>hit the robot colony</i>

47
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:45,233
on Caspia-Nine.

48
00:02:45,266 --> 00:02:46,266
No!

49
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:48,066
O'SHAY:
At maximum hyperspeed,

50
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,100
you can get there
in four hours.

51
00:02:52,266 --> 00:02:55,733
MEN:
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

52
00:02:55,766 --> 00:02:59,233
EMILY:
Father, you have
built-in weapons.

53
00:02:59,266 --> 00:03:00,733
Why don't you
fight them?

54
00:03:00,766 --> 00:03:03,200
FATHER:
I can't fight humans.
You can't either.

55
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,533
Our programming
doesn't allow it.

56
00:03:04,566 --> 00:03:06,733
[GRUNTING]

57
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:10,533
It doesn't stop me
from protecting you!

58
00:03:10,566 --> 00:03:13,733
[GRUNTING]

59
00:03:13,766 --> 00:03:17,500
MOTHER:
Hurry, get into
the space pod.

60
00:03:17,533 --> 00:03:19,733
What about you?
You're coming too, right?

61
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:21,100
We can't, Emily.

62
00:03:21,133 --> 00:03:23,366
We'll divert them
while you get away.

63
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,100
Father, no!

64
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:27,366
Emily, when you're safe,
try to find the Blue Knight.

65
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,400
He will help us!

66
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:29,633
The Blue Knight?

67
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:31,466
Like in those stories?

68
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,233
I thought he was
just make-believe.

69
00:03:33,266 --> 00:03:35,500
Emily, the Blue Knight is real.

70
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:36,500
You've got to find him!

71
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:38,800
He has <i>kokoro.</i>

72
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,466
He can fight humans.

73
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,566
He believes robots
have the right to be free!

74
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,700
Argh!

75
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:50,033
Remember, Emily,
we love you!

76
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:53,033
Father!

77
00:03:58,308 --> 00:04:00,474
MAN:
Ha, ha! Do you know
how much they're worth?

78
00:04:00,508 --> 00:04:01,774
We're talking
big bucks here.

79
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:03,808
These bots
are prototypes.

80
00:04:03,841 --> 00:04:05,474
They have
state-of-the-art intel.

81
00:04:05,508 --> 00:04:07,674
MAN 2:
We'll send them
to the crystal mines on Mars

82
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:09,408
like all
the other robots.

83
00:04:09,441 --> 00:04:11,708
First, remove
their intelligence.

84
00:04:11,741 --> 00:04:13,474
But then we won't
even get half the price!

85
00:04:13,508 --> 00:04:14,541
Quiet!

86
00:04:14,574 --> 00:04:15,574
Look at them,

87
00:04:15,608 --> 00:04:16,708
trying to act
like humans.

88
00:04:16,741 --> 00:04:18,541
It's a disgrace!

89
00:04:18,574 --> 00:04:20,774
Robots should be programmed
to take orders,

90
00:04:20,808 --> 00:04:22,008
not to think for themselves.

91
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:23,374
Is that clear?

92
00:04:23,408 --> 00:04:26,508
Whatever you say,
Mr. Katari.

93
00:04:26,541 --> 00:04:28,241
You're the boss.

94
00:04:32,041 --> 00:04:33,274
[BELL RINGING]

95
00:04:33,308 --> 00:04:34,274
A distress signal!

96
00:04:36,708 --> 00:04:38,308
Gotta fly!

97
00:04:47,408 --> 00:04:48,508
Dad. Mom.

98
00:04:50,008 --> 00:04:51,974
EMILY:
Oh!

99
00:04:52,008 --> 00:04:53,208
[SCREAMS]

100
00:04:57,041 --> 00:04:58,474
Don't be afraid.

101
00:04:58,508 --> 00:05:00,374
I only wanna help you.

102
00:05:00,408 --> 00:05:02,974
Kinda cramped
in there, isn't it?

103
00:05:03,008 --> 00:05:04,608
Why don't you come outside?

104
00:05:07,308 --> 00:05:08,941
How did you know
I was here?

105
00:05:08,974 --> 00:05:11,508
I've been
searching for you.

106
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:13,474
My sensors picked up
your signal.

107
00:05:13,508 --> 00:05:14,474
Are you okay?

108
00:05:19,841 --> 00:05:21,941
[SOBBING]

109
00:05:21,974 --> 00:05:23,374
We were attacked

110
00:05:23,408 --> 00:05:24,874
by a bunch
of space raiders.

111
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:26,774
They got my mom and dad!

112
00:05:26,808 --> 00:05:30,374
I know.
I heard the report.

113
00:05:30,408 --> 00:05:33,308
Don't worry. I've been tracking
the space raiders for days.

114
00:05:33,341 --> 00:05:34,708
That's why I'm here.

115
00:05:34,741 --> 00:05:35,808
I'll find your parents

116
00:05:35,841 --> 00:05:37,241
and bring them back,
I promise.

117
00:05:37,274 --> 00:05:38,708
But first I'm gonna
take you

118
00:05:38,741 --> 00:05:40,641
some place
that's safe.

119
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,374
You mean you're gonna
blast the space raiders?

120
00:05:42,408 --> 00:05:44,241
That's great!
I wanna fight too.

121
00:05:44,274 --> 00:05:45,708
Take it easy!

122
00:05:45,741 --> 00:05:46,808
I know you're upset,

123
00:05:46,841 --> 00:05:48,308
but fighting's
not the answer.

124
00:05:48,341 --> 00:05:50,341
Humans do bad things
sometimes,

125
00:05:50,374 --> 00:05:51,408
but we can't just
vaporize them

126
00:05:51,441 --> 00:05:52,741
every time
there's a problem!

127
00:05:52,774 --> 00:05:54,908
You're not programmed
to fight, are you?

128
00:05:54,941 --> 00:05:56,841
That's not the point.

129
00:05:56,874 --> 00:05:58,741
It's just that we need to show
humans a more peaceful--

130
00:05:58,774 --> 00:06:00,008
I don't care!

131
00:06:00,041 --> 00:06:00,874
If humans
attack robots,

132
00:06:00,908 --> 00:06:03,574
then robots have
the right to fight back!

133
00:06:03,608 --> 00:06:04,974
That's what
the Blue Knight says.

134
00:06:05,008 --> 00:06:07,008
My father told me
all about the Blue Knight.

135
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:08,508
But you don't know him.

136
00:06:08,541 --> 00:06:09,708
I know enough.

137
00:06:09,741 --> 00:06:11,808
He can change regular robots
into battle-bots

138
00:06:11,841 --> 00:06:13,908
and reset them
for combat mode.

139
00:06:13,941 --> 00:06:17,441
You see, if he reprograms me,
I can go and save my parents!

140
00:06:17,474 --> 00:06:19,741
But...
I'll save them.

141
00:06:19,774 --> 00:06:21,008
They're my family.

142
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,274
I'm not going
to wait around

143
00:06:22,308 --> 00:06:23,874
for someone
to do this for me.

144
00:06:23,908 --> 00:06:26,374
When Blue Knight changes me,

145
00:06:26,408 --> 00:06:28,374
I'll have weapons
and armor and all kinds of--

146
00:06:28,408 --> 00:06:30,708
Listen, Emily, it's not
just about weapons.

147
00:06:30,741 --> 00:06:31,974
He'll change the way
you think.

148
00:06:32,008 --> 00:06:33,808
They change who you are.

149
00:06:33,841 --> 00:06:35,474
I don't want that
to happen to you.

150
00:06:35,508 --> 00:06:36,741
Why?

151
00:06:38,874 --> 00:06:40,441
Because I like you.

152
00:06:40,474 --> 00:06:41,674
You're a special robot.
That's why.

153
00:06:41,708 --> 00:06:44,441
[SIGHS]

154
00:06:44,474 --> 00:06:45,674
Hmm.

155
00:06:45,708 --> 00:06:46,841
[BOTH GASP]

156
00:06:46,874 --> 00:06:50,208
[RUMBLING]

157
00:06:58,608 --> 00:06:59,808
EMILY:
Space raiders!

158
00:06:59,841 --> 00:07:00,841
ASTRO:
They're back!

159
00:07:08,732 --> 00:07:11,098
[♪]

160
00:07:11,132 --> 00:07:12,465
EMILY:
Where's it taking us?

161
00:07:12,498 --> 00:07:14,832
ASTRO:
It's going to be okay.

162
00:07:14,865 --> 00:07:16,465
I know where we are.

163
00:07:17,932 --> 00:07:19,698
Astro.

164
00:07:19,732 --> 00:07:22,565
Blue Knight.
You really are the Blue Knight!

165
00:07:22,598 --> 00:07:25,365
Oh, I thought the space raiders
got us too.

166
00:07:25,398 --> 00:07:26,565
I've been looking
for you.

167
00:07:26,598 --> 00:07:28,032
You've found me.

168
00:07:32,432 --> 00:07:34,865
All right, unlock
the force field.

169
00:07:34,898 --> 00:07:38,732
[ROARING & SIZZLING]

170
00:07:46,098 --> 00:07:47,965
KATARI [OVER PA]: <i>You are now</i>
<i>my personal possessions.</i>

171
00:07:47,998 --> 00:07:49,932
<i>From here you'll be</i>
<i>shipped off</i>

172
00:07:49,965 --> 00:07:50,965
<i>to the Martian</i>
<i>crystal mines,</i>

173
00:07:50,998 --> 00:07:54,698
<i>where you will work</i>
<i>until you rust.</i>

174
00:07:54,732 --> 00:07:58,732
That's the only thing
robots are good for.

175
00:07:58,765 --> 00:08:02,398
KATARI:
<i>If you try to escape or fail</i>
<i>to cooperate in any way,</i>

176
00:08:02,432 --> 00:08:05,465
<i>you will be</i>
<i>instantly vaporized.</i>

177
00:08:05,498 --> 00:08:09,698
[LAUGHS EVILLY]

178
00:08:09,732 --> 00:08:12,498
EMILY: <i>My mother and father</i>
<i>are in danger.</i>

179
00:08:12,532 --> 00:08:14,065
Please change me
into a battle-bot

180
00:08:14,098 --> 00:08:15,398
so I can help them.

181
00:08:15,432 --> 00:08:17,865
Don't do it!
She's not a warrior.

182
00:08:17,898 --> 00:08:19,798
You can see she wasn't
made for fighting.

183
00:08:22,632 --> 00:08:24,898
I will send a squadron
to find your parents.

184
00:08:24,932 --> 00:08:26,898
You can wait here
at my base.

185
00:08:26,932 --> 00:08:28,898
My troops will make sure
that you're safe.

186
00:08:28,932 --> 00:08:30,798
I don't wanna be safe!

187
00:08:30,832 --> 00:08:33,098
I can't just wait here
while my family's in danger.

188
00:08:33,132 --> 00:08:35,998
Listen, Emily, you were
not meant to fight.

189
00:08:36,032 --> 00:08:39,898
I know I'm programmed to obey,
but I can change, Astro.

190
00:08:39,932 --> 00:08:41,898
EMILY:
You understand,
don't you, Blue Knight?

191
00:08:41,932 --> 00:08:43,898
My father told me
so many stories about you.

192
00:08:43,932 --> 00:08:45,865
I want to join you.

193
00:08:45,898 --> 00:08:47,365
ASTRO:
Tell her no,
Blue Knight.

194
00:08:47,398 --> 00:08:48,398
Don't change her
into a battle-bot.

195
00:08:48,432 --> 00:08:50,498
EMILY: But I need
to be strong now.

196
00:08:50,532 --> 00:08:51,332
BLUE KNIGHT:
Enough!

197
00:08:53,065 --> 00:08:55,498
In my camp,
every robot is free.

198
00:08:55,532 --> 00:08:57,765
If they are afraid,
we protect them.

199
00:08:57,798 --> 00:09:00,465
And if they want to join
our fight, we welcome them.

200
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:02,565
No one can control
another robot

201
00:09:02,598 --> 00:09:03,798
or tell them
what to do,

202
00:09:03,832 --> 00:09:06,565
even if their intentions
are good, Astro.

203
00:09:09,832 --> 00:09:11,498
The choice is yours, Emily,

204
00:09:11,532 --> 00:09:13,532
but you would be taking
a great risk.

205
00:09:13,565 --> 00:09:15,565
Think about it
very carefully.

206
00:09:19,832 --> 00:09:20,632
I've decided.

207
00:09:20,665 --> 00:09:23,565
I want to be a class-one
battle-bot.

208
00:09:23,598 --> 00:09:25,532
Prepare to transform.

209
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,065
ROBOT:
Blue Knight!

210
00:09:27,098 --> 00:09:30,498
Blue Knight! We've located
the space raiders.

211
00:09:32,432 --> 00:09:33,765
ROBOT:
This is their base.

212
00:09:33,798 --> 00:09:34,932
When the force field is up,

213
00:09:34,965 --> 00:09:37,565
it's invisible
to most scan systems.

214
00:09:37,598 --> 00:09:38,798
That's why it's so hard to find.

215
00:09:41,065 --> 00:09:42,832
We've finally penetrated
their cloaking system,

216
00:09:42,865 --> 00:09:43,732
and this is what we found:

217
00:09:43,765 --> 00:09:47,498
a suspension cage
with captured robots

218
00:09:47,532 --> 00:09:49,932
and a particle generator
ready to blast them.

219
00:09:49,965 --> 00:09:51,032
ROBOT 2:
That's their security.

220
00:09:51,065 --> 00:09:52,632
If they're threatened,

221
00:09:52,665 --> 00:09:54,432
that generator can destroy
the robots in an instant.

222
00:09:54,465 --> 00:09:56,065
[GASPS]

223
00:09:56,098 --> 00:09:57,898
BLUE KNIGHT:
So we can't just go
charging in there.

224
00:09:57,932 --> 00:09:59,732
We need a plan.

225
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:02,498
ASTRO:
Let me see
if I can find a weakness.

226
00:10:02,532 --> 00:10:04,098
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

227
00:10:04,132 --> 00:10:07,798
ASTRO:
This is the power source
for their particle generator.

228
00:10:07,832 --> 00:10:10,032
I can take it out
if you draw their attention,

229
00:10:10,065 --> 00:10:11,532
but we'll have to work fast.

230
00:10:11,565 --> 00:10:13,598
It'll take precise teamwork.

231
00:10:13,632 --> 00:10:16,632
So you've decided
to join our fight. Finally.

232
00:10:16,665 --> 00:10:19,398
I'll save these robots,
but I won't hurt humans.

233
00:10:19,432 --> 00:10:21,465
Hmm. I understand.

234
00:10:21,498 --> 00:10:23,632
You haven't changed
at all, Astro.

235
00:10:23,665 --> 00:10:26,132
We may not see eye to eye,

236
00:10:26,165 --> 00:10:28,498
but today we fight
side by side.

237
00:10:28,532 --> 00:10:29,898
Right.

238
00:10:29,932 --> 00:10:32,065
Did you analyze
the force field?

239
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:33,898
NORQUEST:
26 times.

240
00:10:33,932 --> 00:10:35,132
It's practically impossible
to break through.

241
00:10:35,165 --> 00:10:36,698
BLUE KNIGHT:
Practically?

242
00:10:36,732 --> 00:10:38,598
NORQUEST:
There's a tiny flaw
in the grid.

243
00:10:38,632 --> 00:10:40,632
And how do we
bust through that flaw?

244
00:10:40,665 --> 00:10:41,765
We need a robot

245
00:10:41,798 --> 00:10:43,632
traveling
at sub-light speeds.

246
00:10:43,665 --> 00:10:44,898
Right.

247
00:10:44,932 --> 00:10:45,932
That might be able

248
00:10:45,965 --> 00:10:47,398
to break through at this spot.

249
00:10:47,432 --> 00:10:48,632
If the robot is boosted
with power

250
00:10:48,665 --> 00:10:49,765
from your sword

251
00:10:49,798 --> 00:10:51,365
and Astro's
arm cannon,

252
00:10:51,398 --> 00:10:52,632
it may penetrate
the grid.

253
00:10:52,665 --> 00:10:55,598
I can do it. I'll go.

254
00:10:55,632 --> 00:10:58,698
Small robot, Crusher.
You'd be smashed to pieces.

255
00:10:58,732 --> 00:10:59,932
[SIGHS]

256
00:10:59,965 --> 00:11:01,465
All right, I'll do it.

257
00:11:01,498 --> 00:11:04,732
Astro, even you can't
do two things at once.

258
00:11:04,765 --> 00:11:07,365
You heard Norquest:

259
00:11:07,398 --> 00:11:09,132
we'll need your arm cannon
to accelerate the robot,

260
00:11:09,165 --> 00:11:10,598
and all my knights
are too big.

261
00:11:10,632 --> 00:11:12,098
I can do it!

262
00:11:12,132 --> 00:11:13,932
No, Emily.

263
00:11:13,965 --> 00:11:16,765
Even if I turned you into
a battle-bot, it wouldn't work.

264
00:11:16,798 --> 00:11:19,798
You're used to thinking
like a child, not a warrior.

265
00:11:19,832 --> 00:11:21,632
You can't do it,
Emily.

266
00:11:21,665 --> 00:11:22,698
Yes, I can!

267
00:11:22,732 --> 00:11:25,698
I am the only one
small enough.

268
00:11:25,732 --> 00:11:26,898
NORQUEST:
It's true.

269
00:11:26,932 --> 00:11:28,498
I just scanned
the database.

270
00:11:28,532 --> 00:11:31,065
There's no other
suitable candidate.

271
00:11:31,098 --> 00:11:33,098
I'll do whatever it takes!

272
00:11:35,698 --> 00:11:36,798
Shadow,

273
00:11:36,832 --> 00:11:39,132
can she be transformed
into a warrior

274
00:11:39,165 --> 00:11:40,798
in time
for this mission?

275
00:11:40,832 --> 00:11:42,532
Theoretically, it's possible.

276
00:11:42,565 --> 00:11:43,898
But without training,

277
00:11:43,932 --> 00:11:46,832
her old fears would come back
and paralyze her.

278
00:11:46,865 --> 00:11:49,798
To avoid that, we'd need
to remove her memory.

279
00:11:49,832 --> 00:11:51,865
[GASPS]

280
00:11:51,898 --> 00:11:53,532
You can't do that!

281
00:11:53,565 --> 00:11:54,598
Without her memories,

282
00:11:54,632 --> 00:11:56,598
she wouldn't even
be herself anymore.

283
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:58,632
We can return
her memories later,

284
00:11:58,665 --> 00:12:00,665
but the process
is not perfected.

285
00:12:00,698 --> 00:12:02,798
She'd be risking everything.

286
00:12:02,832 --> 00:12:03,932
It's too much!

287
00:12:03,965 --> 00:12:05,498
I'll take that risk!

288
00:12:05,532 --> 00:12:08,498
Make whatever changes
you need to make. I'm ready.

289
00:12:11,798 --> 00:12:15,565
SHADOW:
Once you become a warrior,
you will feel no fear.

290
00:12:15,598 --> 00:12:18,798
But you will also
feel no joy or pleasure.

291
00:12:18,832 --> 00:12:22,565
I understand. Transform me
into a battle-bot.

292
00:12:22,598 --> 00:12:24,732
SHADOW:
Let us begin.

293
00:12:31,565 --> 00:12:33,665
[BEEPING]

294
00:12:43,432 --> 00:12:45,798
EMILY [WITH ROBOTIC VOICE]:
My system
is at maximum capacity.

295
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:47,698
I am ready for the mission.

296
00:12:47,732 --> 00:12:49,698
Let nothing stand in my way.

297
00:12:51,732 --> 00:12:53,365
Emily!

298
00:13:06,873 --> 00:13:10,106
ROBOT:
We're at 57 kilo-kliks
and closing.

299
00:13:11,973 --> 00:13:13,240
BLUE KNIGHT:
It's time, Astro.

300
00:13:13,273 --> 00:13:15,006
Is Emily ready for launch?

301
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:17,240
ROBOT:
Yes, sir,
locked on target.

302
00:13:17,273 --> 00:13:18,306
BLUE KNIGHT:
Start the attack!

303
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,240
ROBOT:
Affirmative.

304
00:13:23,006 --> 00:13:25,140
All right, Astro, let's
give her a power boost.

305
00:13:25,173 --> 00:13:26,173
Right!

306
00:13:27,273 --> 00:13:29,573
Let justice prevail!

307
00:13:29,606 --> 00:13:31,306
BOTH:
Yahhhh!

308
00:13:49,106 --> 00:13:50,773
What was that?

309
00:13:50,806 --> 00:13:52,140
MAN:
Something broke
through the force field.

310
00:13:52,173 --> 00:13:53,173
It's coming toward us!

311
00:13:53,206 --> 00:13:54,973
KATARI:
Blast it out of the sky!

312
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:15,040
[YELLS]

313
00:14:15,073 --> 00:14:15,873
Arggh!

314
00:14:18,273 --> 00:14:21,040
MAN:
The force field
is breaking down!

315
00:14:21,073 --> 00:14:23,073
We're all clear!

316
00:14:23,106 --> 00:14:24,540
ASTRO:
Let's rocket!

317
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:35,173
[GRUNTS]

318
00:14:35,206 --> 00:14:36,940
Another foolish robot!

319
00:14:36,973 --> 00:14:39,240
[GRUNTING]

320
00:14:44,073 --> 00:14:46,140
Another captive!

321
00:14:46,173 --> 00:14:47,740
ALL:
Arggh!

322
00:14:52,173 --> 00:14:53,840
Activate the vaporizer!

323
00:14:53,873 --> 00:14:56,240
Destroy all the robots!

324
00:14:56,273 --> 00:14:59,240
MAN:
Yes, sir. It'll take 20 seconds
to reach full power.

325
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:03,006
ASTRO:
<i>The power source</i>
<i>is straight ahead!</i>

326
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:05,006
MAN:
Nineteen, eighteen,

327
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:07,006
<i>seventeen,</i>

328
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:10,940
<i>sixteen, fifteen, fourteen,</i>

329
00:15:10,973 --> 00:15:15,640
<i>thirteen, twelve, eleven,</i>

330
00:15:15,673 --> 00:15:18,606
<i>ten, nine,</i>

331
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:19,640
[WHIMPERS]
<i>eight,</i>

332
00:15:19,673 --> 00:15:22,840
<i>seven, six,</i>

333
00:15:22,873 --> 00:15:24,606
ASTRO:
<i>Target locked.</i>
<i>five,</i>

334
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:29,740
ASTRO: <i>Fire!</i>
<i>four, three, two, one.</i>

335
00:15:29,773 --> 00:15:30,873
And vaporize!

336
00:15:30,906 --> 00:15:31,973
Huh? We lost our power!

337
00:15:32,006 --> 00:15:34,240
[SCREAMING, GROANING]

338
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:38,873
Surprise!

339
00:15:38,906 --> 00:15:41,273
Arggh!

340
00:15:41,306 --> 00:15:44,106
[SCREAMING]

341
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:50,140
[SIGHS]

342
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:53,806
BLUE KNIGHT:
Emily! Behind you!

343
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,806
He said Emily!

344
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,073
Hold it!

345
00:16:07,673 --> 00:16:08,673
Emily!

346
00:16:08,706 --> 00:16:10,973
Is that you,
sweetheart?

347
00:16:11,006 --> 00:16:14,573
You are correct.
I am your child unit.

348
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:17,640
Serial number 815-Z.

349
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:22,673
Everyone, get in the ship.
We're taking you out of here.

350
00:16:22,706 --> 00:16:24,173
Emily's been
reprogrammed.

351
00:16:24,206 --> 00:16:25,240
Now, come on!

352
00:16:25,273 --> 00:16:26,306
Who did this?

353
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:27,840
ASTRO:
It was her own decision.

354
00:16:27,873 --> 00:16:29,240
There's no time to explain.

355
00:16:29,273 --> 00:16:31,140
You've got to get on the ship.
Now, hurry!

356
00:16:31,173 --> 00:16:32,173
Huh? Arggh!

357
00:16:34,340 --> 00:16:36,706
You're not going anywhere!

358
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,240
ASTRO:
Blue Knight!

359
00:16:39,273 --> 00:16:41,640
I've got your back!

360
00:16:44,273 --> 00:16:46,040
Time to turn this battle around.

361
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:50,073
EMILY:
Wait here.

362
00:16:50,106 --> 00:16:51,540
[BOTH GASP]

363
00:16:55,606 --> 00:16:57,840
You're scrap metal!

364
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:03,006
EMILY:
Yahhh!

365
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:07,206
Arggh!

366
00:17:08,740 --> 00:17:11,306
Yahhh!

367
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:13,306
[GROWLS]

368
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,106
Yahhh!

369
00:17:22,106 --> 00:17:24,073
EMILY'S PARENTS:
Emily! Emily!

370
00:17:24,106 --> 00:17:26,806
[GRUNTING]

371
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:29,073
Foolish robots!

372
00:17:29,106 --> 00:17:33,940
[GRUNTING & WHIMPERING]

373
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,673
[BOTH GASP]

374
00:17:39,606 --> 00:17:40,773
[BLUE KNIGHT GROWLS]

375
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:48,573
Go ahead!

376
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,173
Blue Knight!

377
00:17:55,973 --> 00:17:58,740
You can have him, Astro.

378
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,640
EMILY'S FATHER:
Emily!

379
00:18:02,673 --> 00:18:05,073
Wake up, Emily!
Can you hear me?

380
00:18:05,106 --> 00:18:06,006
EMILY'S MOTHER:
Emily!

381
00:18:11,106 --> 00:18:13,840
SHADOW:
The reconfiguration
is complete.

382
00:18:13,873 --> 00:18:16,573
We've changed Emily back
to her original form

383
00:18:16,606 --> 00:18:18,073
and uploaded her memory data.

384
00:18:18,106 --> 00:18:20,606
ASTRO:
Then why doesn't
she wake up?

385
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,606
Why can't you
activate her program?

386
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:25,240
SHADOW:
I told you it was
an experimental procedure.

387
00:18:25,273 --> 00:18:27,140
Of course, we can
override her system

388
00:18:27,173 --> 00:18:28,840
and get her to respond
mechanically,

389
00:18:28,873 --> 00:18:31,606
but her brain, the part of her
that used to be Emily,

390
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:33,240
that part may never return.

391
00:18:33,273 --> 00:18:34,706
[BOTH GASP]

392
00:18:40,973 --> 00:18:43,773
I know this was Emily's idea.

393
00:18:43,806 --> 00:18:45,940
She chose to make this decision.

394
00:18:45,973 --> 00:18:49,906
But she was just an innocent
robot on the inside.

395
00:18:49,940 --> 00:18:51,940
Why did she have to become
so tough on the outside?

396
00:18:51,973 --> 00:18:54,773
[ASTRO GROANS]

397
00:18:58,740 --> 00:18:59,940
EMILY'S MOTHER:
Emily?

398
00:18:59,973 --> 00:19:02,806
Emily, we're here with you.

399
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:06,806
We know you did this for us
because we needed you,

400
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:07,906
but we need you now!

401
00:19:11,906 --> 00:19:14,206
Oh!

402
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:15,606
Emily!

403
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,240
[GASPS]

404
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:24,606
Father. Mother.
You're all right now.

405
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:27,006
MOTHER:
Because you saved us.
Don't you remember?

406
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:29,073
FATHER:
They changed you
into a warrior.

407
00:19:29,106 --> 00:19:34,340
I kind of remember.
But it was all so dark.

408
00:19:34,373 --> 00:19:38,940
I felt so alone, and all
I could think of was fighting.

409
00:19:38,973 --> 00:19:44,340
Astro, I don't want to be
a warrior. Never again.

410
00:19:44,373 --> 00:19:45,973
I just want to be
with my family.

411
00:19:46,006 --> 00:19:48,206
Emily.

412
00:19:54,706 --> 00:19:56,306
BLUE KNIGHT:
If Astro were
to join our cause,

413
00:19:56,340 --> 00:19:58,706
we'd be so much
stronger.

414
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:00,740
SHADOW:
But his methods
are different than ours.

415
00:20:00,773 --> 00:20:02,173
How could we get him
to join us?

416
00:20:02,206 --> 00:20:03,240
By going to planet Earth.

417
00:20:03,273 --> 00:20:04,340
That's where Astro
is based,

418
00:20:04,373 --> 00:20:05,873
and that's where
we should be.

419
00:20:05,906 --> 00:20:08,173
It is time to move
our operations.

420
00:20:08,206 --> 00:20:12,073
That could lead to all-out war
between robots and humans.

421
00:20:12,106 --> 00:20:13,973
Is that what you want?

422
00:20:14,006 --> 00:20:17,673
I am a knight.
I only fight in defense.

423
00:20:17,706 --> 00:20:21,006
But if robots
are treated like slaves,

424
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:24,240
then I will do whatever
it takes to set them free.

425
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,706
We were all created on Earth.

426
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:32,706
Tell the other knights...
we're going home.

427
00:20:38,706 --> 00:20:40,640
[♪]

